<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-939] optional binary fields throw NPE on default byte[] getters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-939</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As it turns out, the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-894&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-894&lt;/a&gt; in 0.5.0-rc0 is broken wrt optional binary fields, the BufferFor&amp;lt;Field&amp;gt; methods work fine and return a null ByteBuffer, however the get&amp;lt;Field&amp;gt; will NPE, for example a call to the accessor for the unfilled optional binary field ColumnEntry.data causes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.NullPointerException&lt;br/&gt;
       at org.apache.thrift.TBaseHelper.wrapsFullArray(TBaseHelper.java:256)&lt;br/&gt;
       at org.apache.thrift.TBaseHelper.rightSize(TBaseHelper.java:273)&lt;br/&gt;
       at com.twitter.service.metastore.gen.ColumnEntry.getData(Unknown Source)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
